<TEXT>
president roh taewoo said monday he is 
postponing a national referendum on his performance because 
violent leftist forces are trying to use it to overthrow the 
government 
in an address on national television roh said it would not be 
of help to the country to hold a national referendum for my 
performance in office at this juncture 
roh said the referendum which had been widely expected sometime 
next month will be held sometime in the future but he gave no date 
the president had been expected this week to announce the date to 
keep a promise he made during 1987 presidential elections 
it was not clear if roh was backing away from the referendum 
because of concern about potential unrest or because he feared the 
government could not win the vote and might be forced into new 
elections 
some opposition and dissident groups had been demanding roh stake 
his presidency on the referendum and step down if defeated it is 
not clear if roh a former general could win a referendum 
the government had said earlier that roh would not step down if 
he were defeated but some senior administration officials have 
conceded a defeat would put pressure on him to call new elections 
roh said antigovernment forces were attempting to use the vote 
to organize violent protests and topple the government dissidents 
and radical students have organized violent demonstrations in recent 
weeks but they have little popular support 
the people are worried roh said leftist forces are trying 
to use the referendum as a foothold to overthrow the free democratic 
system 
south koreas divided opposition parties were split over rohs 
decision 
the party of peace and democracy of kim daejung welcomed the 
decision while the reunification democratic party of kim youngsam 
said it would accept a temporary delay 
kim youngsam had been pushing for a referendum after predicting 
roh would lose kim daejung opposed a referendum apparently 
because kim youngsams party had overtaken his party in opinion 
polls and could win presidential elections 
the two kims are bitter rivals who split the opposition vote in 
december 1987 presidential elections allowing roh to win with 36 
percent of the vote roh promised during the election campaign to 
hold a referendum after his first year in office to give voters a 
chance to evaluate his performance 
roh also said national opinion was split on whether to hold 
the referendum 
one opposition party said the referendum should be on the 
question of policy matters while another party said it should be on 
a vote of noconfidence he said 
in view of these developments the proposed referendum 
originally intended to stabilize the political situation and 
solidify democratization has lost its meaning roh said 
