<TEXT>
here is a look at el salvador a 
nation nestled in the soft pacific curve of central america a land 
with a history of violence that is named for jesus 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
geography the country covers 8260 square miles about the size 
of massachusetts it is rugged a land of volcanoes and lakes and 
rich soil it is about 950 miles southwest of miami 950 miles 
southeast of brownsville texas 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
population its more than 5 million people are mainly roman 
catholic and mestizo people of both indian and spanish heritage 
more than 500000 of its residents have fled its 9yearold civil 
war most of them to the united states 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
history it was conquered in 1525 by the spanish it became 
independent on sept 15 1821 and joined the central american 
federation which later split into the nations that now make up 
central america 
it was ruled for most of this century by a landowning oligarchy 
in alliance with the military 
in 1932 a peasant rebellion organized by farabundo marti was 
crushed by a military regime that killed 30000 people the leader 
of that rebellion inspired the present guerrillas the farabundo 
marti national liberation front 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
economy it is mostly agricultural with coffee the main cash 
crop in the 1960s and 1970s it became a manufacturing center for 
the central american market its largest input is us military and 
civil aid which comes to 15 million a day 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the war the conflict began in 1979 when a group of young 
officers overthrew former president gen carlos humberto romero a 
junta tried to impose agrarian and social reforms but dissatisfied 
leftists began a rebellion in late 1979 
the conflict has led to more than 70000 deaths most of them 
civilian and many suspected leftists killed by rightwing death 
squads in the early 1980s 
in 1984 jose napoleon duarte a christian democrat became the 
first popularly elected president in 50 years sundays election 
marks the first time salvadorans have had a chance to replace an 
incumbent civilian government with a different party 
</TEXT>
