presidents more modest proposal would cost about 200000 
the democrats have assailed those figures saying past increases 
in the minimum wage have not caused significant job losses but the 
congressional budget office in a report sent to hawkins on friday 
estimated that raising the minimum to 465 would cause a loss of 
from 125000 to 250000 jobs 
