the tibetan people are a member of the big family of the 
chinese nation any attempt to internationalize the tibetan question 
on the excuse of human rights is firmly opposed by the chinese 
government and will never succeed the statement said 
its strong language is in keeping with chinas policy of harshly 
rejecting outside criticism of its actions in tibet which it claims 
has been part of chinas territory since the 13th century 
many tibetans say they enjoyed de facto independence before 
chinese communist troops entered in 1950 they accuse the chinese of 
human rights violations and of trying to destroy tibets 
buddhistbased culture 
the european parliament passed its resolution thursday about the 
martial law china imposed march 8 after three days of antichinese 
violence in the tibetan capital lhasa at least 12 people were 
killed in the fourth bloody tibetanchinese confrontation in the 
past 18 months 
the parliament also appealed to foreign ministers of the 
12member european community to offer their mediation 
we are firmly opposed to and will by no means accept such 
mediation the chinese statement said no foreign government 
organization or individual is allowed to meddle in the question of 
negotiations between the chinese central government and the dalai 
lama the dalai lama is a selfexile many tibetans consider their 
temporal and spiritual leader 
the us senate which also acted thursday has approved 
nonbinding resolutions in the past urging the state department to 
pressure china to end alleged human rights violations in tibet 
two days after china imposed martial law on tibet the us state 
department issued a statement of concern which china dismissed as 
interference 
the chinese government is entirely justified and above reproach 
in taking the necessary measures to uphold law and maintain order 
the chinese legislative committee said 
it reiterated chinas willingness to hold talks with the dalai 
lama but ruled out independence or autonomy for the remote region 
we strongly demand that the european parliament immediately 
stop its interference in chinas internal affairs so as to prevent 
doing any harm to our bilateral relations it said 
it similarly warned the us senate to act in the interests of 
safeguarding chineseus relations 
